    <text id="A6306T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Evans writes that he enjoyed his last visit and urges Sibert to visit Ella in
                    Staunton next week. He also reports on family news.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-06-16">June 16 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Mollie</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I <orig reg="arrived">rived</orig> home Safely &amp; had quite a <orig
                        reg="pleasant">plesent</orig> ride. <orig reg="Though">Tho</orig> I did Not
                    Enjoy it as much as the ride we had up the River in the Evening. I did Enjoy it
                    So much. I did wish you could have come back with me. Ella will <orig reg="move"
                        >moove</orig> this week &amp; why <orig reg="can't">cant</orig> you come
                    up with me when I came down <orig reg="again">a gain</orig> you &amp; Ella
                    can then go up to the Furnace <orig reg="together">to gether</orig> it would be
                    such a <orig reg="pleasant">plesent</orig> trip for you you could Spend a week
                    or so in the mountains <pb n="2"/>very <orig reg="pleasantly">plesently</orig> I
                    would Not want you to Stay too long for I would <orig reg="rather"
                    >ragther</orig> for you to Spend all your time in Staunton. I think you told me
                    Some time ago that you <orig reg="intended">Entended</orig> to Spend the Summer
                    with Ella I hope you will &amp; make up your mind to come back with me
                    Saturday a week if we live <orig reg="won't">wont</orig> you? I know your Ma
                    will Not object to your coming</p>

                <p>You ask me Several times if I enjoyed my visit Yes and I <orig reg="always">all
                        ways</orig> Enjoy my visits I am <orig reg="always">all ways</orig> happy
                    when with you my love the greatest <orig reg="pleasure">plesure</orig> I have in
                    this world is <orig reg="visiting">viseting</orig> you <pb n="3"/>at your home
                    never think I am not happy or <orig reg="don't">dont</orig> Enjoy <orig
                        reg="myself">my self</orig> for I do, &amp; I love you with all the
                        <orig reg="strength">Strenth</orig> of my Soul &amp; mind I love you
                    with true devotion of my heart. Magnus &amp; Ella will be down Saturday if
                    they live. Tell your Ma Mr Sheets <orig reg="said">Sad</orig> he would take Miss
                    Maggie's Photographs down with him <orig reg="today">to day</orig> my love to
                    your Ma. love to all</p>

                <p>I Send a <orig reg="loving">loveing</orig> Kiss to you. I love you with all my
                    heart &amp; Soul may God Bless you. Good bye</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>D H Evans</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
